{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de00a3af-96a7-45fa-9404-b2d441f6a96d","content":"CLR activation logs aren't the right tool for this. They only track **how the .NET runtime itself is loaded** (e.g., which CLR version the shim selects). They won't reveal anything about a `NullReferenceException` in your application code.\n\n**To diagnose a NullReferenceException, try these instead:**\n\n1. **Stack trace** — check the exception's stack trace to find the exact line/method where the null dereference occurs.\n2. **`dotnet-dump`** — collect and analyze a crash dump.\n3. **`dotnet-trace`** — capture events around startup.\n4. **Debugger** — attach with VS/VS Code/`dotnet-debugger` and break on the exception.\n\nIf you share the stack trace or crash dump, I can help pinpoint the bug. Or if you suspect the **wrong CLR version is loading** (causing the crash), I can invoke the CLR activation debugging skill for that specific angle.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"116bcfe1-1cbf-494b-b2cc-b2c2ea604fce","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking me to analyze CLR activation logs to diagnose a NullReferenceException. However, CLR activation logs are about runtime loading/selection — they wouldn't diagnose a NullReferenceException. Let me check if the clr-activation-debugging skill is relevant here.\n\nThe clr-activation-debugging skill description says: \"Diagnoses .NET Framework CLR activation issues using CLR activation logs (CLRLoad logs) produced by mscoree.dll. Use when: the shim picks the wrong runtime, fails to load any runtime, shows unexpected .NET 3.5 Feature-on-Demand (FOD) dialogs...\"\n\n\nA NullReferenceException that occurs after the application starts isn't a CLR activation problem — it's an application-level exception that happens well after the runtime has already loaded successfully. CLR activation logs won't help here, so I should clarify this distinction with the user rather than applying a tool designed for runtime loading issues.","outputTokens":477},"id":"36fb1843-c090-4e8a-bfda-7032004caae1","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:17:19.437Z","parentId":"86d2a45b-a45b-49e5-8767-2b9cf13b73f7"}
